step.action:
Auto-save triage decisions to Val's memory sidecar (no user prompt required):
1. Append to {memory_path}/validator-sidecar/decision-log.md: ### [YYYY-MM-DD] Triage: {N} findings processed
- **Agent:** validator - **Workflow:** triage-findings - **Status:** recorded - **Related:** {comma-separated list of source story keys}
Triaged {N} findings. Created {X} new stories: {list of new_key (title)}. Added {Y} to existing stories: {list of existing_key}. Dismissed {Z}. Timing: {count} NOW (inject), {count} NEXT SPRINT (P0), {count} BACKLOG. Mapping: {new_key → source_key for each created story}
2. Replace body of {memory_path}/validator-sidecar/conversation-context.md (preserve header above first ---): Last session: Triage of {N} findings from {source_count} stories. Date: {YYYY-MM-DD}. Created: {X} stories. Added: {Y}. Dismissed: {Z}. Urgent: {count} stories flagged for immediate sprint injection.
If _memory/validator-sidecar/ directory or files don't exist, create them with standard headers. If writing fails, log warning and continue — memory save is non-blocking.
